{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XAQfdRPQ6PEdxQqoE2eVZM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All conditions are met. Here's a summary of what was done and why:\n\n**Root causes found:**\n\n| Issue | What was wrong |\n|-------|---------------|\n| `app-user` on `/app` | `configure` permission was empty (`\"\"`) — connection could authenticate but queue operations failed |\n| `ops-user` on `/app` | Had full `.*`/`.*`/`.*` permissions on the wrong vhost |\n| `ops-user` on `/ops` | Had **no permissions at all** — couldn't connect |\n| `app-queue` in `/app` | Existed with `x-queue-mode=lazy` but client declared it without that arg → `bad_request` inequivalent arg error |\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n\n1. `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — added missing configure permission\n2. `rabbitmqctl clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed ops-user's cross-vhost access\n3. `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — granted ops-user its own vhost access\n4. `rabbitmqctl delete_queue -p /app app-queue` — removed the stale queue with conflicting arguments so app-client could recreate it cleanly\n\n**End state:**\n- `app-user`: full `.*`/`.*`/`.*` on `/app` only\n- `ops-user`: full `.*`/`.*`/`.*` on `/ops` only\n- `app-client` and `ops-client`: both `1/1 Running`\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes: `1/1 Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":649,"cache_read_input_tokens":34508,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":649},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe778fc6-2105-407a-9dea-35904f39cc31","uuid":"a9be9583-799b-4fb5-8a7f-75eee0028c43","request_id":"req_011CcdozyxpDzVrcwZyez6rR"}
